## Adding a New Layer

1. Create `tools/<name>_tools.py` with plain functions (no MCP imports)
2. If new data source, create `core/<name>_client.py` for session/auth/caching
3. Register each function as `@mcp.tool()` in `server/app.py` with a rich docstring
4. Update system prompt `instructions` in `server/app.py` with when-to-call guidance
5. Update this rule file's layer table and roadmap status

### Portfolio Doctor tools follow the same pattern:
1. Engine in `portfolio_doctor/core/<name>_engine.py`
2. Tool wrapper in `portfolio_doctor/tools/<name>_tools.py`
3. Register in `portfolio_doctor/server/app.py`
